I always ask "Why are you so sure that governments, NASA, scientists all around the world are lying to us? What do they have to gain from that?"
"Because they want us to stay ignorant."
"But what do they gain from us believing that specific lie? Many people can't agree on what to eat for dinner - how should so many people agree on the exact specifics of such an enourmous lie?"

I also like to point out that in the 4th century BC Aristotle already proved the earth was a sphere without satellites and later Eratosthenes figured out the radius mathematically that was only slightly corrected by modern technology. Other unrelated ancient scholars' research agrees with these findings - what reason would THEY have to forge all that data?

snippet.textDisplay:
As a programmer, here is my argument. The computer behind how an airplane works is based on a global earth. If the premise was already wrong, how is it that the airplane gets to its destination correctly.

Its just like a tax app. If the algorithm and the parameters of the tax algorithm is already wrong, it would give us incorrect tax amount. Computers cannot just make up stuff. Someone has to program it. And the people behind the tax app need to have rules and guidelines.

Same goes with the people behind making the airplane or its computers.
